{{Quote|One does not need to be Jedi to learn the ways of the Force. I suspect it cares little for our codes and philosophies.|[[Kreia]]|<ref name="Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''</ref>}}
'''Force Adepts''' were [[The Force/Legends|Force]]-[[Force-sensitive/Legends|wielders]] of all [[Species/Legends|species]] with varying [[Force power/Legends|powers and abilities]]. Some of these Force Adepts were known to wield [[Force weapon]]s such as [[Quarterstaff/Legends|quarterstaffs]] imbued with [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], which were able to withstand and inflicted more damage than a [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] strike. Often they were with little to no formal [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] training in the Force and often coming from primitive [[Planet/Legends|planets]].

==Description==
Force Adepts were individuals strong in [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], but who were either untrained or followed a different Force tradition to the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]]. Force Adepts came from many different cultures and belief systems and viewed their connection to the Force as more mysterious and supernatural. Some hailed from primitive cultures, trained as a [[Shaman/Legends|shaman]] for their people. Others were from well-known Force traditions, such as the ecological [[Priest/Legends|priests]] who tended the [[Mother Jungle/Legends|Mother Jungle]] of [[Ithor/Legends|Ithor]], the [[Witches of Dathomir]], the [[Jensaarai/Legends|Jensaarai]], or the [[Sorcerers of Tund/Legends|Sorcerers of Tund]]. These traditions had different beliefs on the nature of the Force, and their own codes of conduct.<ref name="RPG-Core">''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Core Rulebook]]''</ref>

Discovering a power inside themselves that they did not fully comprehend, Force Adepts first learned to master their own ability to affect the physical world. If they hailed from primitive or backwater planets, their training could be haphazard due to a lack of traditional education in how to master their abilities. Adepts could be seen by their people as holy or godlike due to their abilities. If they were a member of a more formalized Force tradition, they were trained as others before them had been. Some referred to the Force by the name it was commonly known as, but some called it by different terms.<ref name="RPG-Core" /> 

Force Adepts often became adventurers in the wider galaxy as a result of striving to learn more about the Force and their connection to it. Others were forced from their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworlds]], hunted by those who did not understand or feared their power. Adepts resigned themselves to being either revered or hated for their abilities, depending on what planet or region they found themselves in. Some hid their powers, either because they did not understand them, or were afraid of how others would treat them when they found out. Most Force Adepts followed the [[Light side of the Force/Legends|light side]] of the Force, or the equivalent version in their belief system. Few embraced the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]]. Force Adepts were known by many names, including wizards, shamans, witches, or prophets.<ref name="RPG-Core" />

Adepts had the ability in imbue inanimate objects with the Force. The most common items were unpowered melee weapons, such as [[Knife/Legends|knives]], [[Club/Legends|clubs]], or [[Quarterstaff/Legends|quarterstaves]], giving the adept an edge when using them in combat. They could also imbue object to create [[Force artifact/Legends|Force talismans]] which helped to defend them from Force-based attacks. Force adepts also often relied on more mundane skills to complement their Force abilities.<ref name="RPG-Core" />

==Behind the scenes==
Force Adept was one the eight starting classes established in the [[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Core Rulebook|Core Rulebook]] for [[Wizards of the Coast]]'s ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]]''. [[Valara Saar]], a [[Human/Legends|Human]], served as the character example for the class.<ref name="RPG-Core" />

The second group of Force adepts is the concept used for a class in the [[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Revised Core Rulebook]]. In [[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Saga Edition Core Rulebook|Saga Edition]] the Force adept would be turned into a prestige class with specific rules (such as item imbuing), while an official guide for converting between editions suggested the scout class for the "primitive" variety of Force adepts.

